HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 411
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Tyler Sparks, 2025
Salutatorian of Hampshire Unit School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Tyler Sparks is one such exceptional student, who was recently named the
Salutatorian of the 2025 graduating class at Hampshire Unit School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Sparks has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Tyler Sparks has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities,
including baseball, FBLA, Beta Club, FCA, the Boy Scouts of America, and the Columbia
Mayor's Youth Council; and
WHEREAS, his time at Hampshire Unit School saw him volunteer generously to help
with the Well Food Bank, construct community library boxes, spend quality time with the elderly,
and package cake boxes for needy families; and
WHEREAS, apart from his superlative scholastic labors, Mr. Sparks exhibits his
extraordinary industriousness by acting as a customer service lead at Food Lion; and
WHEREAS, Tyler Sparks's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for his future success at Columbia State Community College, where he will study finance; and
